    "body": "## Summary\n- update the TVM submodule to include the TempDirectory race-condition fix for debug temp dir creation\n- avoid secondary cleanup failures when TempDirectory initialization aborts partway through\n- make NVCC artifact paths unique when `cuda.kernels_output_dir` is shared across concurrent compilations\n\n## Context\nConcurrent CUDA compilation could fail while creating `/tmp/tvm-debug-mode-tempdirs` when multiple processes entered the debug-tempdir path at the same time. Once that happened, `TempDirectory.__del__` could also raise a follow-up `AttributeError` on a partially initialized object.\n\nThis change pulls in the TVM-side fix and updates TileLang's NVCC helper to resolve per-invocation artifact paths safely when a shared kernels output directory is configured.\n\n## Validation\n- `pytest -q testing/python/contrib/test_tilelang_contrib_nvcc.py`\n- direct multiprocessing verification for `tvm.contrib.utils.TempDirectory` race handling and partial-initialization cleanup\n- `python -m py_compile tilelang/contrib/nvcc.py 3rdparty/tvm/python/tvm/contrib/utils.py 3rdparty/tvm/python/tvm/contrib/nvcc.py 3rdparty/tvm/tests/python/contrib/test_util.py`\n\n## Notes\nThe vendored `3rdparty/tvm` pytest suite was not run in this environment because the required `libtvm.so` / `libtvm_runtime.so` artifacts were not available locally.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Updated a third-party subproject pointer (no functional changes).\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Centralized CUDA kernel artifact path handling to improve temporary output management.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Marked a GPU-specific test to run only when CUDA is available and adjusted test entrypoint to use the standard test runner.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
